# Cursor Rules -- Resume Website

This repository represents a **production-quality personal engineering
portfolio**.

Code must reflect:

-   senior engineering practices
-   QA discipline
-   strong testing
-   performance awareness
-   accessibility standards

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Stack

Next.js 15\
React 18\
TypeScript (strict)\
Styled Components\
Material UI

Testing: Jest\
React Testing Library\
jest-axe

Quality: ESLint\
Prettier\
Danger\
SonarCloud

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# General Rules

-   Prefer improving existing code instead of rewriting large sections
-   Never introduce `any`
-   Maintain TypeScript strict mode
-   Never bypass lint, test, or build errors
-   Avoid unnecessary dependencies
-   Keep components small and readable
-   Prefer incremental changes

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Security

Never commit secrets.

Environment variables must:

-   exist in `.env.local`
-   be documented in `env.example`
-   be accessed via `src/utils/env.ts`

Never access `process.env` directly inside components.

Never render user input with `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Architecture

Project structure:

src/ components/ data/ pages/ types/ utils/ tests/ styles/

Rules:

-   one component per file
-   extract reusable logic into hooks
-   keep components under \~150 lines

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Content

All static content must live inside:

src/data/

Components should not hardcode content.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# TypeScript

Strict mode required.

Rules:

-   avoid `any`
-   prefer `unknown` + guards
-   define interfaces for props
-   use `as const` for config objects

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# React

Use functional components only.

Avoid class components.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Next.js

Use `next/image` for images.

Use dynamic imports for heavy components.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# SEO

All pages must include metadata.

Metadata should be centralized in:

src/data/profile.ts

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Accessibility

Use:

-   semantic HTML
-   alt text for images
-   correct heading hierarchy
-   ARIA attributes when needed

Accessibility tests should use jest-axe.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Testing

Framework:

Jest\
React Testing Library

Location:

src/tests/

Coverage target:

80%+

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Code Quality

Before committing:

yarn lint\
yarn test\
yarn build

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Git Hooks

Husky runs:

pre-commit → lint + format\
pre-push → tests + build

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CI

GitHub Actions pipeline:

tests\
lint\
build\
SonarCloud\
Danger

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Goal

This repository should demonstrate:

clean architecture\
strong QA practices\
performance optimization\
accessibility awareness\
modern frontend engineering
